<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="39.[826,1467,184,926]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[828,996,263,287]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,996,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Li.gi.lac.to.ba.cil'lus. L. 
<taxonomicName box="[1256,1335,263,287]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" rank="variety" variety="ligare">
v. 
<emphasis box="[1278,1335,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">ligare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to tie, unite; N.L. masc. n. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beijerinck" authorityYear="1901" box="[968,1103,295,319]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1103,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Lactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a bacterial genus name; N.L. masc. n. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[856,1024,326,350]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[856,1024,326,350]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a lactobacillus with a host-associated life style).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="39.[826,1467,184,926]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[935,1102,403,427]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[935,1102,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are homofermentative, their mol% G+C content is between 32.5 and 43.3. Several 
<taxonomicName box="[1301,1466,434,458]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1466,434,458]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species include strains that are motile. Most 
<taxonomicName box="[1298,1466,466,490]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1466,466,490]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have been isolated from animals and humans and are adapted to vertebrate hosts. Several strains of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1299,1466,528,552]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1466,528,552]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
express urease, this enzyme is the most powerful bacterial tool to withstand gastric acidity; in lactobacilli, urease activity is associated with a vertebrate host-adapted lifestyle [
<bibRefCitation author="Kakimoto S &amp; Okazaki K &amp; Sakane T &amp; Imai K &amp; Sumino Y" box="[1360,1403,622,646]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" pagination="1111 - 1117" refId="ref68994" refString="210. Kakimoto S, Okazaki K, Sakane T, Imai K, Sumino Y et al. Isolation and taxonomie characterization of acid urease-producing bacteria. Agric Biol Chem 1989; 53: 1111 - 1117." type="journal article" year="1989">210</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Krumbeck JA &amp; Marsteller NL &amp; Frese SA &amp; Peterson DA &amp; Tait AE" box="[1413,1456,622,646]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" pagination="2172 - 2184" refId="ref69033" refString="211. Krumbeck JA, Marsteller NL, Frese SA, Peterson DA, Ramer- Tait AE et al. Characterization of the ecologica l role of genes mediating acid resistance in L actobacillus reuteri during colonization of the gastrointestina l tract. Environ Microbiol 2016; 18: 2172 - 2184." type="journal article" year="2016">211</bibRefCitation>
]. Several 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1088,653,677]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[917,1088,653,677]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species also commonly occur in fermented foods and are used commercially as starter cultures or probiotic cultures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[826,1467,184,926]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">
A phylogenetic tree on the basis of 16S rRNA genes of all species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[1039,1205,793,817]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1205,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provided in 
<figureCitation box="[1355,1463,793,817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[185,216,1617,1636]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,181,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[264,1323,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 6. Gene family presence/absence patterns in Lactobacillaceae and Leuconostocaceae. Each column represents a gene family presence/absence pattern in species of Lactobacillaceae and Leuconostoaceae, where presence is indicated with a dot. The absolute number of gene families that conform to each pattern is visualized in the marginal bar plot at the top. Separations between phylogroups are indicated with horizontal black lines. We defined genes that were present in all genomes of a clade and in none of the genomes outside of that clade as ‘signature genes’ (dark blue); other genes are shown in light blue. Only presence/absence patterns followed by four or more gene families are shown. Patterns of presence in a single species or all species are not shown. Unassigned species are clusters of closely related genomes which could not be assigned to a known species due to low whole-genome similarity to a type strain and/or low 16S rRNA similarity to a type strain." pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Figure S6J</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="39.[826,1467,184,926]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">
The 
<typeStatus box="[877,924,840,864]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">type</typeStatus>
species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1045,1331,839,863]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="salivarius" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1045,1331,839,863]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus salivarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1339,1463,839,863]" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" box="[828,1001,870,894]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,1001,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">Ligilactobacillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously referred to as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1335,1466,870,894]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Ligilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="salivarius">
<emphasis box="[1335,1466,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="2821">L. salivarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
